6:
I feel bad making you trek out to the
borderlands, but I need to make
sure everyone's doing well.
18:
I wonder how the elemental gems
will mix with the soil here.
28:
We should be close to the village.
And yet, I can sense no signs of life.
43: Is that what destroyed the village?
68:
Wait... I don't see any bodies. War
always leaves a trail of human
suffering, but here... There's nothing.
85:
I was the one who discovered them.
There's a web of tunnels inside
connected to other ruins and
unknown danger, so I'd always
warned the villagers away, but...
100:
You don't know how happy I am to
see you! What happened? What
forced you to evacuate to these
ruins?
105:
...Will nothing quench the royal
family's thirst for blood?
108:
Well... They didn't get even a drop
this time. Folks from the western
border sounded the alarm, and we
hid every last villager away in these
ruins.
112:
I didn't know borderlanders
communicated between villages.
117:
I took a leaf out of your book,
Rakisha, and decided to embark on
my own journey across the
borderlands.
118:
There wasn't a single village that
would refuse shelter to a friend of
yours. And I'd often stay up late into
the night, talking and trading
information on irrigation techniques,
ruins—everything.
124:
What can I say? You kindled the
spirit of adventure in me. And good
thing too. It was someone out west
who told me about these ruins.
126:
We—as a village—did some thinking
when you left. About how to survive,
no matter what ills are blown our
way.
127:
Right now, we're just fleeing the
storm, but...
133:
You're resilient. Far stronger than I
ever gave you credit for.
136:
Oh, right! What's happened to the
village? I hope the fields are okay...
138: I'd call this the opposite of "okay..."
140:
Oh well. We're just gonna have to
rebuild and resow the fields. Or
actually, we should consider
relocating first...
144:
Looks like I had nothing to worry
about.
148:
Here. This dust was crafted from
elemental gems. Mix it into the
earth, and it'll help barren land
sustain life.
151:
I never knew gems had that kind of
power...
156:
You'll probably need to adjust the
formula so it's compatible with the
local soil. And that's going to take
research and experimentation.
157:
Also, at the end of the day, your
labors might not bear fruit. If you
decide against investing the time
and energy, I wouldn't blame you.
160:
You've brought us a seed of hope,
Rakisha. Of course we'll try and
nurture it!
164:
I really need to stop
underestimating you all.
167:
—How much should we use?
—We should save at least half for
research!
—We'd better start collecting gems
ourselves!
170: Things are looking up, aren't they?
174:
I'd always thought the desert sucked
the strength out of people and
made them weak. But maybe I just
never realized how deep their roots
ran...
177:
Seems like I wasn't a miracle worker
after all.
183:
They grew strong because you
cared for them, Rakisha.
184:
You gave them courage and
direction. There are few gifts more
valuable.
187: You really are a sweet-talker, Light.
190:
Rakisha? Mind sticking around for a
bit? Just until we get things up and
running.
199:
From here on out, their journeys will
serve to spread seeds of hope all
over the desert.
202:
Do you think I could bring a few of
these villagers to Starview?
207:
As long as you keep it to "a few."
Stella's never been known to turn
anyone away.
217:
...You're the most generous souls I've
ever met.
